Talks between the Union of Nurses and the national and county governments over nurses&rsquo; pay were concluded on Saturday night, with a deal expected to be signed on Sunday.The deal could signal an end to the nurses&rsquo; strike that has paralyzed operations in public health facilities for the past six days.Read: Government fails to avert health workers' strike Details of the deal remain scanty although the nurses were demanding the implementation of the Collective Bargaining Agreement (CBA) of 2013 and the Recognition Agreement with the national and county governments.Both nurses and doctors have rejected a salaries commission report on job evaluation, saying it does not indicate what they should earn.